com.serena.dmclient.objects
Interface BaselineTemplateRule

All Superinterfaces:
DimensionsObject
public interface BaselineTemplateRule
extends DimensionsObject

Represents a Dimensions Baseline Template Rule.

A baseline template rule details the item or request type(s) and the associated state that are used to determine which items are selected when creating a baseline.

Note: The special Dimensions Item Type ("*") may be used to define a rule that affects all item types in the product.

getStateSelector

RuleStateSelector getStateSelector()
                                   throws DimensionsRuntimeException
Returns the selector that indicates
  • which lifecycle state the last edited item revision should be at, in order to be included in the baseline. Applies when multiple items of the selected type are present at the lifecycle state specified in the baseline template rule.
  • which lifecycle state the request should be at, in order to be included in the baseline.

Returns:
the state selector
Throws:
DimensionsRuntimeException - if connection error or internal error occurs
